description: Russia said on Friday that major powers needed a new approach to North Korea, accusing the United States and its allies of ratchetting up military tensions in Asia and seeking to "strangle" the reclusive state.
title: After veto, Russia says big powers need to stop 'strangling' North Korea

description: Joe Biden on Friday acknowledged "the pain being felt" by many Arab Americans over the war in Gaza and over U.S. support of Israel and its military offensive that has left Arabs, Muslims and anti-war activists angry and disappointed.
title: Biden acknowledges 'pain' of Arab Americans over war in Gaza

description: President Joe Biden said on Friday the U.S. will impose costs for Russia's "appalling attempts" to use Americans as bargaining chips in a statement to mark the one-year anniversary of Wall Street Journal reporter Evan Gershkovich's arrest in Russia.
title: Biden threatens Russia with costs on Evan Gershkovich arrest anniversary

description: Explosions were heard in Ukraine's Ivano-Frankivsk and Khmelnytskyi regions and the city of Dnipro on Friday morning as Russian cruise missiles were spotted in Ukrainian air space, media outlet Suspilne reported.
title: Blasts reported in several Ukrainian regions amid Russian missile attack

description: Chinese investigators arrived in Pakistan on Friday to join a probe into the killing of five Chinese nationals in a suicide attack, Pakistan's interior ministry said, seeking to stem assaults threatening Islamabad's drive to modernise the economy.
title: China joins probe into deadly Pakistan suicide attack on its nationals

description: Taiwan's navy chief, Tang Hua, will visit the United States from next week to attend a military ceremony and discuss how to boost bilateral naval cooperation as China raises threats toward the island, six people briefed on the trip said.
title: Exclusive: Taiwan's navy chief to visit U.S. next week, sources say

description: Famine is both a risk and quite possibly present in at least some areas of the northern Gaza Strip, a senior U.S. State Department official said on Friday, while adding that a scarcity of trucks was an obstacle to getting more aid into the densely populated enclave under Israel siege.
title: Famine is 'quite possibly' in some areas of northern Gaza, U.S. official says

description: France has asked about 45 foreign countries to contribute several thousand extra military, police and civilian personnel to help safeguard the Paris Olympics this summer, government sources said on Friday, amid a complex geopolitical and security outlook.
title: France to boost Olympics security with foreign military, police support

description: Before the Gaza war, Palestinian fisherman Jalal Qaraan navigated his small boat for long distances in search of a good catch. These days he says merely casting his nets could be deadly if he draws the wrath of the Israeli navy.
title: Gaza fisherman braves Israeli navy fire to support his family

description: King Charles is due to make his first public appearance at a royal event since his cancer diagnosis on Sunday, but the likely absence of son Prince William and the heir's wife Kate will spotlight how depleted the monarchy has become.
title: Illness, scandal and discord leave UK royal family looking depleted

description: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi is likely to prioritise completion of free trade deals with Britain and Oman in the first 100 days of the next government if he wins upcoming elections as opinion polls predict, two government sources said.
title: India keen on trade deals with Britain, Oman early in Modi's probable third term, sources say

description: India's main opposition party said on Friday it had been asked to pay an additional 18.2 billion rupees ($218 million) in taxes, which it called an attempt by the tax department to financially cripple it weeks before general elections.
title: India's Congress says facing 'tax terrorism' after second tax notice

description: When a French minister compared Italy's nationalist Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni last year to the leader of the French far right, the Italian premier rang French President Emmanuel Macron to complain.
title: Insight: Meloni, Le Pen rift mars far right's prospects of wielding EU power

description: Israel sustained its aerial and ground bombardment of the Gaza Strip on Friday, killing dozens of Palestinians, as fighting raged around Gaza City's main Al Shifa hospital, Palestinian officials and the Israeli military said.
title: Israel kills dozens in airstrikes across the Gaza Strip

description: The Israeli military said on Friday it had killed Ali Abed Akhsan Naim, deputy commander of Hezbollah's rocket and missiles unit, in an air strike in the area of Bazouriye in Lebanon.
title: Israeli military says it killed deputy commander of Hezbollah rocket and missiles unit

description: The Italian airforce said on Friday it intercepted unidentified aircraft flying over international waters in the Baltic Sea, and two defence sources in Rome identified them as Russian planes.
title: Italy intercepts Russian planes over Baltic Sea, defence sources say

description: Thousands of Jordanians rallied near the Israeli embassy on Thursday in a fifth day of large protests against Israel, calling for an end to Jordan's unpopular peace treaty with its neighbour to the west.
title: Jordanians protest against peace treaty with Israel in fresh rallies

description: King Charles, who is undergoing treatment for cancer, told Bahamian Prime Minister Philip Davis on Thursday that he hopes to visit the Commonwealth nation next year, the prime minister's office said in a statement.
title: King Charles hopes to visit The Bahamas next year, prime minister's office says

description: Ukraine's military will need to mobilise fewer people than initially expected to fend off Russia's two-year-old invasion, Kyiv's top general said on Friday.
title: Kyiv's top general says Ukraine needs fewer troops than expected

description: The biggest operational crane on the U.S. Eastern Seaboard towered over Baltimore's port on Friday, ready to begin clearing the wreckage of the Francis Scott Key Bridge days after a cargo ship crashed into it, sending the span crashing into the harbor.
title: Massive crane put in place to clear Baltimore bridge debris as crews assess damage

description: A Moscow district court ruled on Friday that the ninth suspect in the March 22 concert hall attack in which more than 140 people were killed should be held in custody until May 22 pending trial.
title: Moscow court puts ninth suspect in concert hall attack under pre-trial custody

description: Canada's Niagara region has proactively declared a state of emergency ahead of a rare total solar eclipse on April 8 that is expected to gather massive crowds to areas in and around the region's popular waterfalls.
title: Niagara region declares state of emergency out of caution ahead of rare eclipse

description: The whole village of Kuriga ran towards the convoy of buses shouting "Our children are back!" and "Alhamdulillah," meaning "Thank you, God", to welcome home more than 100 students and staff who were abducted this month in Nigeria's northwest.
title: Nigerian village celebrates the return of kidnapped students

description: North Korea has no interest in dialogue with Japan, state media KCNA reported on Friday, citing foreign minister Choe Son Hui.
title: North Korea rules out any meetings with Japanese officials, KCNA says

description: Catholic devotees were nailed to crosses in sweltering heat north of the Philippines capital Manila on Good Friday in a re-enactment of Jesus Christ's crucifixion.
title: Philippines' Catholic devotees nailed to crosses to re-enact crucifixion

description: The Philippines is not seeking a fight or trouble in the South China Sea but will not be cowed into silence, submission, or subservience, its defence ministry said Friday, in its latest show of defiance in a heated row with China.
title: Philippines says it will not yield to submission in row with 'patronising' China

description: Pope Francis will not attend a Good Friday procession at Rome's Colosseum to protect his health ahead of other Easter week engagements, the Vatican said.
title: Pope Francis skips Good Friday procession at Rome's Colosseum to protect health, Vatican says

description: Pope Francis presided over a Good Friday service in St Peter's Basilica ahead of a night-time procession at Rome's Colosseum for the most sombre day in the Christian calendar, marking Jesus' death by crucifixion.
title: Pope leads Good Friday service ahead of Colosseum procession

description: Russian prosecutors have asked the justice ministry to label Alla Pugacheva, the queen of Soviet pop music, as a "foreign agent", the state RIA news agency reported.
title: Pugacheva, queen of Soviet pop, likely to be labelled a 'foreign agent' in Russia

description: NATO member Romania said it had found fragments of what appeared to be a drone on a farm near the river Danube and the border with Ukraine late on Thursday.
title: Romania says it finds drone fragments near border with Ukraine

description: A Russian court has remanded journalist Antonina Favorskaya in custody for two months after she was charged with participation in an extremist organisation, the Moscow court service said.
title: Russia remands journalist in custody for two months for links to Navalny group

description: Russian forces attacked infrastructure sites early on Friday in Kamianske district near the central Ukrainian city of Dnipro and at least one person was injured, the regional governor said.
title: Russian forces attacking infrastructure near Dnipro city, regional governor says

description: Russia's move to effectively disband the panel of experts monitoring longstanding United Nations sanctions against North Korea points to a "grim future" for the sanctions enforcement, three former members of the panel told Reuters.
title: Russian veto points to 'grim future' for North Korea sanctions enforcement

description: Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov, in an interview published on Friday, said Ukraine's proposed peace plan was pointless as it was based on unacceptable notions like Moscow's withdrawal from areas it has captured.
title: Russia's Lavrov tells newspaper that Ukraine peace plan is pointless

description: Senegal's Constitutional Council on Friday confirmed the presidential election victory of opposition candidate Bassirou Diomaye Faye, paving the way for his inauguration as the country's fifth president.
title: Senegal top court confirms Faye's election victory

description: South Korea is launching a high-speed train service that will reduce the travel time between central Seoul and its outskirts, a project officials hope will encourage more youth to consider homes outside the city, and start having babies.
title: South Korea hopes new speed train links will help boost birthrate

description: South Korea's ambassador to Australia resigned on Friday as questions about his appointment while he is under a corruption probe battered President Yoon Suk Yeol's ruling party less than two weeks from a closely fought parliamentary election.
title: South Korea's ambassador to Australia steps down amid investigation controversy

description: Immediate action is needed to "prevent widespread death and total collapse of livelihoods and avert a catastrophic hunger crisis in Sudan," a United Nations-backed global authority on food security warned on Friday.
title: Sudan needs 'immediate action' on hunger to avert widespread death, UN-backed report says

description: A number of civilians and military personnel were killed after Israel and militant groups launched strikes towards the northern Syrian city of Aleppo, the Syrian defence ministry said early on Friday.
title: Syrian army says strikes at Aleppo claim civilian, military lives

description: Tajikistan has detained nine people this week suspected of having links to a mass shooting at a Russian concert hall last Friday and also to the militant Islamist group that claimed responsibility, a Tajik security source told Reuters.
title: Tajikistan detains 9 people over Russian concert hall attack - source

description: Tajikistan's State National Security Committee has detained nine people this week who it believes have links to the Russian concert hall shooting suspects as well as Islamic State Khorasan (ISIS-K), a Tajik security source told Reuters.
title: Tajikistan detains 9 people over Russian concert shooting - source

description: Thailand's government is considering drafting a casino bill and if passed by parliament, it would generate more jobs and state revenue and allow for the creation of a mega entertainment project, Prime Minister Srettha Thavisin said on Friday.
title: Thai PM says legalising casinos good for revenue and jobs, eyes entertainment project

description: Thailand's government said on Friday its 2025 fiscal budget could be adjusted to accommodate its signature 500 billion baht ($13.71 billion) handout scheme.
title: Thailand considers adjusting budget to accommodate $13.7 bln handout scheme

description: Turkey's President Tayyip Erdogan will visit the United States on May 9, a Turkish security official said on Friday, setting the stage for his first White House meeting during the Biden Administration.
title: Turkey's Erdogan to visit U.S. on May 9, security official says

description: Ukraine's air force downed two Russian missiles in the southern port city of Odesa on Friday afternoon, officials said, but debris hit civilian infrastructure, injuring five people.
title: Ukraine downs two Russian missiles over Odesa, five people injured

description: Ukraine has received a $1.5 billion tranche of funding under a World Bank programme, Prime Minister Denys Shmyhal said on Friday, helping it pay for its budget and social spending as it defends itself against the Russian invasion.
title: Ukraine gets $1.5 bln funding tranche under World Bank programme, PM says

description: Ukrainian Foreign Minister Dmytro Kuleba has urged India to stand by Kyiv, saying the nation's close ties with Russia are based on a Soviet legacy that is evaporating, the Financial Times reported on Friday.
title: Ukraine urges India to rethink 'Soviet legacy' of Russia ties, FT reports

description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy on Friday declared his income for 2022 rose to 12.42 million hryvnias ($306,000) from 3.7 million hryvnias the previous year, with the increase attributable to improved rent collection and sale of some government bonds.
title: Ukraine's Zelenskiy reports his income increased in 2022

description: Ultra-Orthodox Jewish parties are resisting pressure to lift exemptions of religious students from military duty, as Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's struggles to preserve his coalition and spread the wartime burden across society fairly.
title: Ultra-Orthodox Israelis resist push for military service

description: The United States in recent days authorized the transfer of billions of dollars worth of bombs and fighter jets to Israel even as it publicly expresses concerns about an anticipated military offensive in Rafah, the Washington Post reported on Friday.
title: US has signed off on more bombs and warplanes for Israel, Washington Post reports

description: The U.S. military said on Thursday that it had destroyed four unmanned drones launched by Iran-backed Houthi forces in Yemen.
title: US military says it destroyed 4 drones launched by Yemen's Houthis

description: The United States said on Friday it is taking steps to impose new visa restrictions on multiple Hong Kong officials over the crackdown on rights and freedoms in the Chinese-ruled territory.
title: US says imposing new visa curbs on Hong Kong officials over rights crackdown

description: The U.S. is asking American companies to stop shipping goods to more than 600 foreign parties over fears the items could be diverted to Russia for use in its invasion of Ukraine, a U.S. official said on Thursday.
title: US takes another step to stem the flow of technology to Russia for weapons

description: President Volodymyr Zelenskiy said in an interview published on Friday that if Ukraine does not get promised U.S. military aid blocked by disputes in Congress, its forces will have to retreat "in small steps".
title: Zelenskiy says without US aid, Ukraine forces will have to retreat
